  "text": "Although GCM results might not be representative of individual points, our results are supported by a number of recent modeling studies. [CITATION_1] found that the net incoming solar heat flux of 18 W m 22 was nearly fully balanced by the gyre circulation of upwelled cold water from the coast. [CITATION_2] found that a combination of mean circulation, with a small contribution from Ekman transport, balanced [CITATION_3] noted the importance of transient features to the SEP's heat budget, as well as the necessity of taking long-term averages. These modeling studies also argued that the eddy heat flux divergence was not spatially coherent, and therefore was unlikely to contribute to the SEP's heat balance as suggested by [CITATION_4] .",
